contentrichtext.text: '''TTF''' may refer to: ==Science and technology== * [[Tetrathiafulvalene]], an organic compound used in electronics * Time to Failure or Time to Treatment Failure, as in cancer chemotherapy * Time to Fire, as in an Airbag deployment * [[Transcription termination factor, RNA polymerase I|Transcription termination factor]], a protein that regulates transcription of genes * [[NK2 homeobox 1|Thyroid transcription factor]], another protein that regulates transcription of genes * [[Trend Type Forecast]], an aviation weather forecast * [[TrueType]], an outline font standard originally developed by Apple Inc. * TTF Motorsports, To The Front Motorsports, Sport Compact racing team from Northeast Nebraska consisting of Grant Hurlbert #85, Jeb Dunklau #65, Ryne Hoffart #23, Jordan Uehling #58, Cameron Meyer #21 and Garet Hurlbert #8. * [[Tumor Treating Fields]] (TTFields). A novel medical therapy to treat cancerous tumors with alternating [[electric field]]s ==Music== * [[Ten Thousand Fists]], an album by the hard rock band Disturbed * [[The Time Frequency]], a Scottish techno band * [[Tunnel Trance Force]], a long-running trance mix CD series from [[Tunnel Records]] * [http://www.theticketfactory.com The Ticket Factory], a UK primary ticket agent, based in Birmingham ==Miscellaneous== * [http://www.theticketfactory.com The Ticket Factory], a UK primary ticket agent, based at the NEC in Birmingham * [[Title Transfer Facility]], a virtual trading point for natural gas in the Netherlands * [[Titus the Fox]], a platform game by Titus Interactive * Trail Technical Feature, a mountain/dirt biking term to describe added trail obstacles that provide an additional challenge * TTF, The IATA airport code for [[Custer Airport]] in Monroe, Michigan, United States * [[Tuvalu Trust Fund]], an international fund developed by Tuvalu, a small, central Pacific island nation * [[Clark Griswold|Typical Tom Fiasco]], a seemingly innocuous event that mushrooms into a failure {{disambig}}
